scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains materials produced by the International Brotherhood of Teamsters Office of the General President. Included are IBT Constitutions and Community Service Suyveys. These materials date from 1883-2001.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The General President supervises the affairs of the union in accordance with the Constitution and is subject to review by the General Executive Board. The General President presides over the IBT Convention which is held every five years. There have been ten General Presidents to date. Ten staff departments report to the Office of the General President. The office of the General President is responsible for enforcing and maintaining the IBT Constitution. Changes to the Constitution are suggested and voted on by delegates to the IBT Convention.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials in this series include the constitutions of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, Chauffeurs, Warehousemen, and Helpers of America in booklet form. The dates range from 1886-2001. Each booklet contains the constitution and bylaws (internal rules and regulations) of the Teamsters Union. Over time the constitution and bylaws are amended and become more extensive as the organization grows in size.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged numerically by Local Union branch numbers.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials in this series include the community service surveys from various local chapters of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, Chauffeurs, Warehousemen, and Helpers of America. The dates range from 1963-1964; all of the materials with the exception of one document are from 1963. The Surveys range from 1-4 pages with descriptions and sometimes photographs from the local chapter's involvement in charitable institutions. In the case that there were no charitable affiliations in the local branch a brief letter stating such is present.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged chronologically. Note: after Box 7 the order restarts.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains the notes of Vice President of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, Walter J. Shea, from 1975 - 1993.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
